Why not pray about it?

00:11:15.129 --> 00:11:18.129
Reflecting on Jesus' ransom sacrifice

00:11:18.129 --> 00:11:23.129
gives us peace and fills our hearts with gratitude.

00:11:23.129 --> 00:11:27.129
I'm sure you'd agree that we need that peace now

00:11:27.129 --> 00:11:29.129
more than ever before.

00:11:29.129 --> 00:11:33.129
After all, this system of things is so volatile.

00:11:33.129 --> 00:11:35.129
It's like a restless sea,

00:11:35.129 --> 00:11:36.129
and on top of that,

00:11:36.129 --> 00:11:40.129
we face stormy tests of our own faith.

00:11:40.129 --> 00:11:43.129
Despite these stressful circumstances,

00:11:43.129 --> 00:11:45.129
as Jehovah's people,

00:11:45.129 --> 00:11:48.129
we have true peace.

00:11:48.129 --> 00:11:51.129
But how is that possible?

00:11:51.129 --> 00:11:53.129
It's because of a special gift

00:11:53.129 --> 00:11:57.129
that Jesus promised to give His disciples.

00:11:57.129 --> 00:11:59.129
What is that gift?

00:11:59.129 --> 00:12:01.129
Well, let's read His encouraging words

00:12:01.129 --> 00:12:04.129
at John chapter 14 and verse 27,

00:12:04.129 --> 00:12:08.129
that were spoken on the night just before His death.

00:12:08.129 --> 00:12:10.129
Jesus said to them,

00:12:10.129 --> 00:12:12.129
I leave you peace.

00:12:12.129 --> 00:12:15.129
I give you my peace.

00:12:15.129 --> 00:12:18.129
I do not give it to you the way that the world gives it.

00:12:18.129 --> 00:12:21.129
Do not let your hearts be troubled,

00:12:21.129 --> 00:12:24.129
nor let them shrink out of fear.

00:12:24.129 --> 00:12:28.129
Yes, Jesus gave His disciples a wonderful gift.

00:12:28.129 --> 00:12:31.129
What was it?

00:12:31.129 --> 00:12:33.129
Peace.

00:12:33.129 --> 00:12:36.129
And this wasn't simply a lack of conflict.

00:12:36.129 --> 00:12:39.129
No, Jesus said I give you my peace.

00:12:39.129 --> 00:12:41.129
And the peace that Jesus had

00:12:41.129 --> 00:12:44.129
didn't depend on His circumstances.

00:12:44.129 --> 00:12:46.129
He experienced inner peace

00:12:46.129 --> 00:12:48.129
because He knew that Jehovah loved

00:12:48.129 --> 00:12:50.129
and approved of Him.

00:12:50.129 --> 00:12:53.129
And Jesus promised His disciples

00:12:53.129 --> 00:12:57.129
that they too would have this same kind of peace.

00:12:57.129 --> 00:13:03.129
Imagine how this must have comforted their anxious hearts.

00:13:03.129 --> 00:13:05.129
And the same is true for us

00:13:05.129 --> 00:13:09.129
as we face the uncertainties of the last days.

00:13:09.129 --> 00:13:13.129
We're blessed to have a peaceful relationship with Jehovah

00:13:13.129 --> 00:13:15.129
based on our faith in the ransom.

00:13:15.129 --> 00:13:18.129
And that gives us hope.

00:13:18.129 --> 00:13:19.129
It allows us to keep calm

00:13:19.129 --> 00:13:23.129
despite the uncertain times we're living in.

00:13:23.129 --> 00:13:26.129
It stabilizes us.

00:13:26.129 --> 00:13:31.129
Notice the poetic way that Psalm 46 and verse 2 expresses it.

00:13:31.129 --> 00:13:35.129
It says, that is why we will not fear.

00:13:35.129 --> 00:13:37.129
Though the earth undergoes change,

00:13:37.129 --> 00:13:41.129
though the mountains topple into the depths of the sea.

00:13:41.129 --> 00:13:43.129
Doesn't this verse remind us

00:13:43.129 --> 00:13:46.129
of the turbulent times we live in?

00:13:46.129 --> 00:13:48.129
In the last days,

00:13:48.129 --> 00:13:52.129
we may see long-standing mountain-like institutions crumble

00:13:52.129 --> 00:13:56.129
as if they were toppling into the sea.

00:13:56.129 --> 00:14:00.129
And yet, how will we respond?

00:14:00.129 --> 00:14:04.129
Well, the verse says, we will not fear.

00:14:04.129 --> 00:14:06.129
Why not?

00:14:06.129 --> 00:14:09.129
Well, verses 5 to 7 tells us the answer.

00:14:09.129 --> 00:14:13.129
It says, God is in the city.

00:14:13.129 --> 00:14:15.129
It cannot be overthrown.

00:14:15.129 --> 00:14:19.129
God will come to its aid at the break of dawn.

00:14:19.129 --> 00:14:21.129
The nations were in an uproar.

00:14:21.129 --> 00:14:23.129
The kingdoms were overthrown.

00:14:23.129 --> 00:14:27.129
He raised His voice and the earth melted.

00:14:27.129 --> 00:14:30.129
Jehovah of armies is with us.

00:14:30.129 --> 00:14:35.129
The God of Jacob is our secure refuge.

00:14:35.129 --> 00:14:39.129
As the uncertainty of this system increases,

00:14:39.129 --> 00:14:42.129
we do not need to be in fear.

00:14:42.129 --> 00:14:47.129
Remember, God is in full control.

00:14:47.129 --> 00:14:50.129
Jehovah of armies is with us.

00:14:50.129 --> 00:14:52.129
He will come to the aid of His people.

00:14:52.129 --> 00:14:56.129
He is our secure refuge.

00:14:56.129 --> 00:15:00.129
But at times, we may still feel anxiety

00:15:00.129 --> 00:15:04.129
because of the events that are happening around us.

00:15:04.129 --> 00:15:08.129
What does the Bible encourage us to do?

00:15:08.129 --> 00:15:11.129
Ep Philippians 4 and verses 6 and 7

00:15:11.129 --> 00:15:16.129
were encouraged to pour out our hearts to Jehovah.

00:15:16.129 --> 00:15:20.129
And when we do that, what will happen?

00:15:20.129 --> 00:15:22.129
According to verse 7,

00:15:22.129 --> 00:15:26.129
we experience something beyond all understanding,

00:15:26.129 --> 00:15:29.129
the peace of God.

00:15:29.129 --> 00:15:33.129
And that peace will keep us calm and stable

00:15:33.129 --> 00:15:37.129
despite the disturbing things taking place.

00:15:37.129 --> 00:15:41.129
Now, doesn't this motivate us to show our appreciation

00:15:41.129 --> 00:15:46.129
for what God and Christ have done for us by means of the ransom?

00:15:46.129 --> 00:15:49.129
One of the ways we can show our gratitude

00:15:49.129 --> 00:15:51.129
is through the preaching work.

00:15:51.129 --> 00:15:56.129
As we preach, we search for friends of peace,

00:15:56.129 --> 00:16:01.129
those who also want to have peace with God.

00:16:01.129 --> 00:16:03.129
So during this memorial season,

00:16:03.129 --> 00:16:07.129
let's invite as many as we can to learn about

00:16:07.129 --> 00:16:10.129
and to appreciate what Jehovah and Christ Jesus

00:16:10.129 --> 00:16:16.049
have done for us by means of the ransom.

00:16:16.049 --> 00:16:18.049
Before we conclude,

00:16:18.049 --> 00:16:20.049
we're happy to announce the release

00:16:20.049 --> 00:16:24.049
of the 2025 Convention Song entitled

00:16:24.049 --> 00:16:27.049
to do your will is my delight.

00:16:27.049 --> 00:16:30.049
The song and lyrics are now available for download

00:16:30.049 --> 00:16:34.049
in JW Library and on JW.org in English

00:16:34.049 --> 00:16:36.049
and eventually in all the languages

00:16:36.049 --> 00:16:39.049
that will hold the convention.

00:16:39.049 --> 00:16:42.049
The governing body would like everyone

00:16:42.049 --> 00:16:46.049
to practice this song before the convention.

00:16:46.049 --> 00:16:48.049
That way, at the convention,

00:16:48.049 --> 00:16:53.049
we can unitedly sing out from the heart.

00:16:53.049 --> 00:16:56.049
Also, if the words are available in your language,

00:16:56.049 --> 00:16:58.049
you're going to be able to sing this song

00:16:58.049 --> 00:17:02.049
at the midweek meetings during the weeks of April 7th

00:17:02.049 --> 00:17:05.049
and 28th of 2025.

00:17:05.049 --> 00:17:10.779
Brothers and sisters, be assured,

00:17:10.779 --> 00:17:14.779
we love you all very much.

00:17:14.779 --> 00:17:18.779
And please, enjoy the rest of the invitation campaign

00:17:18.779 --> 00:17:22.779
and have a wonderful memorial.

00:17:22.779 --> 00:17:25.779
From the world headquarters of Jehovah's Witnesses,

00:17:25.779 --> 00:17:29.779
this is JW Broadcasting.
